HEADWORD: Splenization
<hw>Splen`i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A morbid state of the lung produced by inflammation, in which its
tissue resembles that of the spleen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Splenocele</ent>⟦br⟧
